id: pm-wc0d
title: Add 120-file unit-test cap governance test to ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts
description: "The 120-file-per-directory cap for tests/unit/ is enforced by scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs (--max-files-per-dir 120) and is a documented rule. However, no test in tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts or elsewhere validates that the current unit file count stays at or below 120. With 122 files already in tests/unit/, the gate should fire soon if new tests keep being added — but contributors won't know this until the static gate fails in CI."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:ci","area:tests",governance,quality-gate
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:34.173Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-09T22:05:01.915Z"
assignee: codex-active-pm-cycle-20260610
author: audit-docs-tests-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- A test or note confirms whether 122 files in tests/unit/ is expected to pass the static gate (e.g. subdirectory counting only, or the cap is directory-specific)\n- If tests/unit/ has exceeded the cap: add a failing test + doc explaining the merge strategy\n- If tests/unit/ has a subdirectory that splits load (tests/unit/core/, tests/unit/commands/): document the strategy in TESTING.md"
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: medium
confidence: medium
body: "## Context\nCurrent test file count: ls tests/unit/ | wc -l = 122. The static-quality-gate.mjs applies --max-files-per-dir 120 globally (line 338). So tests/unit/ may already be at the limit.\n\nci-workflow-contract.spec.ts validates pinned action SHAs, CI gate matrix alignment, etc. but has no assertion about tests/unit/ file count.\n\nThe governance rule from memory: 'tests/unit has a 120-file governance cap (merge, don’t add)'. The fact that it is already at 122 files may mean the static gate is failing, or the gate is not recursive to subdirectories. Either way this should be validated explicitly.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- A test or note confirms whether 122 files in tests/unit/ is expected to pass the static gate (e.g. subdirectory counting only, or the cap is directory-specific)\n- If tests/unit/ has exceeded the cap: add a failing test + doc explaining the merge strategy\n- If tests/unit/ has a subdirectory that splits load (tests/unit/core/, tests/unit/commands/): document the strategy in TESTING.md\n\n## Evidence\nls tests/unit/ | wc -l = 122; tests/unit/core/ and tests/unit/commands/ subdirectory exists per ls output; scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs line 338: maxFilesPerDirectory = 120"
